Day of Sun Commemorated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- A seminar was held by the Party for Peace and Unity of Russia, a meeting and a book and photo exhibition were organized by the Austrian preparatory committee to commemorate the Day of the Sun, reading sessions were held by the Chambogo University of Uganda and the Nigerian Group for the Study of the Juche Philosophy and a photo exhibition and film show were arranged by the Pretoria City Committee of the African National Congress of South Africa from March 30 to April 6 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 On display in the venues of the book and photo exhibitions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and photos showing their immortal revolutionary exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the film show watched Korean film "They Have Always Been Together on the Road of Working for the People". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairperson Sazhi Umalatova and Vice-chairman Ivan Shashbiashbili of the above-said Russian party, addressing the seminar, said that Kim Jong Il has successfully defended the socialism and the dignity and sovereignty of the nation with his unique Songun politics, noting that the President made a great contribution to the Korean revolution and the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Erich Zavadil, chairman of the Austrian preparatory committee, in his speech made at a meeting said that the exploits the President performed by founding and developing the DPRK and leading the struggle to accomplish the human cause of independence would be immortal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Pretoria City Committee of the African National Congress of South Africa at the photo exhibition and film show said that as the President performed undying feats for the human cause of independence, the progressive people of the world significantly commemorate the Day of the Sun with the Korean people every year, noting that the President fully supported the peoples of the African countries in their struggle for national independence and the building of a new society.
 Messages to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the functions held in Russia and Austria.

Police Search in Office of Association of Chongryon under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, April 15 (KNS-KCNA) -- Co-representatives of the "People's Solidarity in Osaka Demanding Earlier Normalization of the Relations between Japan and the DPRK" visited the Osaka Prefectural Association of Korean Workers in Commerce in Japan on April 6. They said that the recent police search in the office of the association aroused bitter indignation even among Japanese as it was an unpardonable outrage, a clear proof of the abuse of power.
 They extended solidarity to the Koreans in Japan in their just struggle, denouncing the police authorities for their unreasonable search in the office of the association.
 They read out a message of solidarity in the name of the "People's Solidarity in Osaka Demanding Earlier Normalization of the Relations between Japan and the DPRK" and conveyed it to Ryo Kwang Si, chairman of the association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In another development, the solidarity sent to the Japanese investigation authorities a letter of protest exposing the injustice of the search and demanding measures to prevent its reoccurrence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryo Kwang Si, when meeting with the co-representatives, said that the search perpetrated by the Tokyo Police Agency in the office of the association was a blatant political suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan and an act of throwing a wet blanket over the efforts to normalize the relations between the DPRK and Japan.

Floral Basket to DPRK Embassy in Havana 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Havana, April 15 (KCNA) -- General Raul Castro Ruz, first vice-president of the Council of State and minister of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Cuba, sent a floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Havana on Apr. 14 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.    
Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Papers in editorials Monday warmly welcome the visit of Cambodian King Norodom Sihamoni to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Cambodian king's visit to the DPRK at the invitation of Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, is his first visit after he assumed the royal post, Rodong Sinmun says: It is a clear token of the development of the DPRK-Cambodia friendly relations and support and encouragement to the Korean people in the efforts for making a new leap forward and innovation in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This visit is an expression of the stand and will of the government and people of Cambodia to steadily strengthen and develop bilateral friendship through centuries and generations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the vigorous strivings in Cambodia to build an independent and prosperous new society, the editorial goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cambodian government is boosting friendly and cooperative relations with many countries including Asian countries on the principles of independence, sovereignty, peace, permanent neutrality, territorial integrity and non-alignment in the external activities. The DPRK people rejoice as their own over the successes registered by the Cambodian people in their endeavors to achieve stability and unity of the country and build an independent and prosperous new Cambodia and extend full support and firm solidarity to their cause of justice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cambodian government and people are standing foursquare behind the cause of justice of the people of the DPRK in the energetic strivings to accomplish earlier the cause of the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and the cause of national reunification, true to the Songun policy of leader Kim Jong Il.
 It is the common desire and will of the peoples of the two countries to steadily consolidate and develop bilateral friendship. The DPRK people will exert themselves to the utmost to boost the friendly and cooperative relations with the Cambodian people. Cambodian king's visit to the DPRK will mark an eventful milestone in developing DPRK-Cambodia friendship to a new, higher stage.

Joint Performances of ASFAF Given 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Joint performances of the 24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival were given Sunday at the Pyongyang Grand Theatre, the Ponghwa Art Theatre and the Pyongyang Circus Theatre.
 The performances were appreciated by Kim Yong Nam, Pak Pong Ju, Jon Pyong Ho, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audiences were Ho Jong Man, chief vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), heads of the delegations of overseas Koreans including Ryang Su Jong, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon, foreign guests and other overseas Koreans.
 Put on the stages were hymns of the sun lauding President   Kim Il Sung and songs of boundless reverence for leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A joint performance was given at the Pyongyang Grand Theatre by the art troupes of Koreans from Japan, China and America and the art troupe of the International United Confederation of Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In male solo "Song Dedicated to Marshal Kim Il Sung," the fourth movement "We Pledge" of symphony "Leader Is Always with Us" and female solo "Song of Loyalty", a famous masterpiece, and other pieces, the performers gave a good ideological and artistic representation of ardent yearning and humble reverence for the peerlessly great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A joint performance was given at the Ponghwa Art Theatre by artistes of China, Russia, Cuba, Mongolia, Georgia, Germany, Moldova, Ukraine, Italy, Kazakhstan and the International Delpic Cultural Festival Council. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage were female solo Korean song "Motherland, Prosper", dance "Chervona Ruta," the fourth movement "Glory to General Kim Jong Il" of symphony suite "Long Journey for Songun Leadership" and other numbers.
 At the Pyongyang Circus Theatre acrobats from China, Russia, Mongolia, the Czech Republic and Sweden performed "Plastic Etude with Bowls on Head", "Horizontal Swinging�h and other pieces, acclaimed by the audience for their difficult technical and stunt movements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets were presented to the performers in congratulation of their successful performances.

