Program Indicating Way to National Unity and Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Eight years have passed since Leader Kim Jong Il made public the famous work "Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully through the Great Unity of the Entire Nation" on April 18, Juche 87 (1998).
 In his work he formulated President Kim Il Sung's idea of the great national unity from a new angle and clarified the five-point policy for the great national unity in order to develop the struggle for the great unity of the entire nation on a new stage in accordance with changed political situation and circumstances.
 The five-point policy is to rely on the principle of national independence, to unite under the banner of national reunification, the banner of loving the country and the nation, to improve relations between the north and the south, to struggle against the domination and interference by outside forces and the anti-reunification forces, and to realize mutual visits and contacts of the whole nation, develop dialogue and strengthen solidarity and alliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last eight years, the work, a program for national unity and reunification, has positively inspired the Korean nation in the efforts for the reconciliation, unity and reunification of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The five-point policy has turned the struggle for national unity and reunification into a nation-wide movement and ushered in a new historical era of reconciliation and cooperation between the north and the south and of independent reunification.
 Upholding the historic June 15 joint declaration, the entire nation has energetically advanced toward the independent reunification. And the north-south relations run through with antagonism and confrontation are being converted into a reconciliation and cooperation under the idea of "by our nation itself". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The years have witnessed brisk governmental and non-governmental exchanges between the north and the south. Among them are inter-Korean ministerial talks, grand festivals for national reunification to mark the publication of the June 15 north and south joint declaration, national rallies to observe the August 15 liberation, inter-Korean conference of workers, inter-Korean conference of peasants and reunion of separated families and relatives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year, too, the solidarity and unity have been strengthened through the reunification campaign of the nation including the joint meeting of youths in the north and the south and the north-south conference of women. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are still many difficulties in the reunification campaign including obstructions of the United States. But, the Korean people will certainly accomplish the cause of the independent reunification, upholding the five-point policy for the great unity of the nation.

Significant and Attractive Art Festival
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The 24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival is going on before full houses in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 It has been attended by many world-famous artistes. Among them is Mitsuko Ogasawara who is chief of the musical company of the Japan-Korea Musical and Artistic Interchange Society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is her 22nd participation in the April Spring Friendship Art Festival from the first one in April Juche71 (1982). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She, with ardent reverence for President Kim Il Sung, impressively sang Korean songs including "Star of Korea" and "Leader, the Night Is Far Advanced" and Japanese songs created by her "With Longing for Pyongyang" and "Let's Sing Pyongyang of Tomorrow", delighting the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She, 86 years of age, is in poor health condition. But she sang songs in clear and beautiful voice, getting rousing ovation from the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In her press interview, she said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "I knew well about President Kim Il Sung through publications from my girlhood and was honored with the audience of the President several times.
 I will never forget the informal and benevolent feature of the President who made his valuable time to meet and frankly converse with an ordinary foreigner. 
 My ever deepening respect and missing for the President is the source of strength for me in my 80s to come to this festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival embraces all fields of art including music, dance and acrobatics. This kind of grand international art festival can be held only in the DPRK which has President Kim Il Sung, the greatest man, as the father of the nation and the eternal President.
 This is, indeed, a significant and attractive art festival in which I hope to participate again and again."

Abnormal Snow in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Rain and Snow fell in most parts of the DPRK on Monday due to the effect of depression moving from Huabei of China to the northward of the West Sea of Korea.
 In an interview with KCNA, Ri Chol Su, vice-director of the Central Weather Forecast Institute under the Hydro-Meteorological Service, said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Pyongyang area it snowed from around 06:30 to around 09:00. The snow lied 1 centimeter thick and its precipitation was 2 millimeters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such phenomenon was observed in Korea on April 17, Juche 51 (1962).
 This phenomenon was attributable to the fact that the cold air stratum below zero degree C was nearly 400 meters high from the ground in and around the country. Therefore, the snow formed in the stratosphere fell to the ground without thawing.
 Such abnormal climate is rare to be seen in Pyongyang area.
 In April when the spring comes around, all kinds of flowers bloom and the seeds sowed in March begin to sprout. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The untimely snowfall exerts harmful influence on the growth of the crops and plants.
